cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the backhaul network in cloud radio access networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses advanced multiterminal backhaul compression techniques, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with communication and networking aspects of cloud radio access networks, including interference management and backhaul integration. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the centralized information processing at control units in C-RANs, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the performance of C-RANs in terms of cell-edge throughput, which is related to multimedia applications.
